From: PS4 Linux Baikal Port <noreply@ps4-linux>
Subject: [PATCH] sky2: also skip MSI self-test in APCIE/BPCIE early-bind branch on Baikal

v67b boot proved patch 0005 wasn't enough. Sky2 reaches MSI setup via
the APCIE-assigned-irqs branch (which on Baikal is implemented by the
bpcie southbridge code), not the standard pci_enable_msi() branch:

    sky2 0000:00:14.1: bpcie_assign_irqs(1)            ← APCIE wrapper
    sky2 0000:00:14.1: bpcie_msi_write_msg(...)
    sky2 0000:00:14.1: bpcie_assign_irqs returning 1
    sky2 0000:00:14.1: bpcie_msi_write_msg(...)
    sky2 0000:00:14.1: No interrupt generated using MSI, switching to INTx mode.
    sky2 0000:00:14.1: probe with driver sky2 failed with error -95

Patch 0005 only skipped sky2_test_msi() in the `pci_enable_msi() == 0`
branch — but apcie_assign_irqs(pdev, 1) returned 1 first, so the kernel
never reached the standard branch. The APCIE branch ran sky2_test_msi
unconditionally and failed.

Fix: add the same Baikal-skip clause to the APCIE branch. When the
device is BAIKAL_GBE, set SKY2_HW_USE_AEOLIA_MSI directly (matching
the original branch's success path) and skip the test that the silicon
doesn't support.

The "AEOLIA" name in SKY2_HW_USE_AEOLIA_MSI is a misnomer — it's the
flag for "PS4 southbridge-routed MSI", which covers Aeolia/Belize/Baikal
all the same. Reusing it for Baikal preserves the rest of sky2's IRQ
plumbing (sky2_intr handler dispatch, refill_rx_pending, etc).

After this:
    sky2 0000:00:14.1: PS4 Baikal: B2_CHIP_ID=0x0, forcing YUKON_PRM
    sky2 0000:00:14.1: chip type 0xbd, Yukon-2 OptimaEEE rev 0
    sky2 0000:00:14.1: bpcie_assign_irqs(1) → 1
    sky2 0000:00:14.1: PS4 Baikal: skipping MSI self-test in APCIE branch
    [no more "probe failed -95"]
    eth0: registered Yukon-2 OptimaEEE
---
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/marvell/sky2.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/marvell/sky2.c
@@ -5055,11 +5055,22 @@
 	#ifdef CONFIG_X86_PS4
 	if (pdev->vendor == PCI_VENDOR_ID_SONY &&
 	    apcie_assign_irqs(pdev, 1) > 0) {
-		err = sky2_test_msi(hw);
-		if (err) {
-			apcie_free_irqs(pdev->irq, 1);
-			/* PS4 requires MSI, so if it fails, bail out. */
-			goto err_out_free_netdev;
+		if (pdev->device == PCI_DEVICE_ID_SONY_BAIKAL_GBE) {
+			/* Baikal silicon does not respond to CS_ST_SW_IRQ
+			 * (sky2's MSI test trigger) — skip the test and
+			 * trust the bpcie southbridge MSI routing that
+			 * apcie_assign_irqs just programmed. Real device
+			 * interrupts still deliver normally through bpcie's
+			 * subfunction demux. */
+			dev_info(&pdev->dev, "PS4 Baikal: skipping MSI self-test in APCIE branch\n");
+		} else {
+			err = sky2_test_msi(hw);
+			if (err) {
+				apcie_free_irqs(pdev->irq, 1);
+				/* Aeolia/Belize need a working MSI test —
+				 * if the test fails there, bail out. */
+				goto err_out_free_netdev;
+			}
 		}
 		hw->flags |= SKY2_HW_USE_AEOLIA_MSI;
 	} else
